  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: From Adam to Abraham'
      title: From Adam to Abraham
      number: 1
      content: 'Adam, Seth, Enosh; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Kenan, Mahalalel, Jared; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Enoch, Methuselah, Lamech; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech,
        and Tiras. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Diphath, and Togarmah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Rhodanim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The sons of Ham: Cush, Mizraim, Put, and Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabta, Raamah, and Sabteca. And
        the sons of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Cush fathered Nimrod; he himself began to be mighty on earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Mizraim fathered the Ludim, the Anamim, the Lehabim, the Naphtuhim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the Pathrusim, the Casluhim (from whence the Philistines descended),
        and the Caphtorim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Canaan fathered Zidon his firstborn, and Heth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and the Jebusites, the Amorites, the Girgashites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the Hivites, the Arkites, the Sinites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the Arvadites, the Zemarites, and the Hamathites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arphaxad, Lud, Aram, Uz, Hul, Gether,
        and Meshech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Arphaxad fathered Shelah; and Shelah fathered Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And two sons were born to Eber: the name of the one was Peleg (for
        in his days the earth was divided), and the name of his brother was Joktan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Joktan fathered Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Ebal, Abimael, Sheba, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab; all these were the sons of Joktan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Shem, Arphaxad, Shelah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Eber, Peleg, Reu; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Serug, Nahor, Terah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Abram, that is, Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Abraham: Isaac and Ishmael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'These are their generations: the firstborn of Ishmael, Nebaioth,
        and Kedar, Abdeel, Mibsam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Jetur, Naphish, and Kedmah. These are the sons of Ishmael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And the sons of Keturah, Abraham\u2019s concubine: she gave birth
        to Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. And the sons of Jokshan:
        Sheba and Dedan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the sons of Midian: Ephah, Epher, Enoch, Abida, and Eldaah. All
        these were the sons of Keturah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Abraham fathered Isaac. The sons of Isaac: Esau and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The sons of Esau: Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The sons of Eliphaz: Teman, Omar, Zephi, Gatam, Kenaz, Timna, and
        Amalek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And the sons of Seir: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer,
        and Dishan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And the sons of Lotan: Hori and Homam; and the sister of Lotan was
        Timna. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The sons of Shobal: Alian, Manahath, Ebal, Shephi, and Onam. And
        the sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The sons of Anah: Dishon. And the sons of Dishon: Hamran, Eshban,
        Ithran, and Keran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Jaakan. The sons of Dishan:
        Uz and Aran. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'These are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any king
        reigned over the Israelites: Bela son of Beor, and the name of his city was
        Dinhabah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'When Bela died, Jobab son of Zerah from Bozrah reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'When Jobab died, Husham from the land of the Temanites reigned in
        his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'When Husham died, Hadad son of Bedad, who defeated the Midianites
        in the country of Moab, reigned in his place. And the name of his city was
        Avith.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'When Hadad died, Samlah from Masrekah reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'When Samlah died, Shaul from Rehoboth-by-the-River reigned in his
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'When Shaul died, Baal-Hanan son of Achbor reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'When Baal-Hanan died, Hadad reigned in his place, and the name of
        his city was Pai. And the name of his wife was Mehetabel, daughter of Matred,
        daughter of Me-Zahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'And Hadad died. And the chiefs of Edom were: chiefs Timna, Aliah,
        Jetheth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Magdiel, and Iram. These are the chiefs of Edom. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Genealogy of David'
      title: The Genealogy of David
      number: 1
      content: 'These are the sons of Israel: Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar,
        Zebulun, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The sons of Judah: Er, Onan and Shelah; these three were born to
        him from Bathshua the Canaanite. Now Er, Judah\u2019s firstborn, was evil
        in the sight of Yahweh, and he put him to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Tamar his daughter-in-law bore Perez and Zerah to him. The sons
        of Judah were five in all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The sons of Perez: Hezron and Hamul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sons of Zerah: Zimri, Ethan, Heman, Calcol, and Dara, five in
        all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The son of Carmi: Achar, the troubler of Israel, who acted unfaithfully
        in the matter of the devoted thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the son of Ethan was Azariah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Hezron who were born to him: Jerahmeel, Ram, and Caleb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Ram fathered Amminadab, and Amminadab fathered Nahshon, prince
        of the sons of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Nahshon fathered Salma, and Salma fathered Boaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Boaz fathered Obed, and Obed fathered Jesse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Jesse fathered Eliab his firstborn, Abinadab the second, Shimea
        the third, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Nethanel the fourth, Raddai the fifth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ozem the sixth, David the seventh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And their sisters were Zeruiah and Abigail. The sons of Zeruiah:
        Abishai, Joab, and Asahel, three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Abigail bore Amasa, and the father of Amasa was Jether the Ishmaelite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Caleb the son of Hezron fathered children by Azubah his wife
        and by Jerioth. And these were her sons: Jesher, Shobab, and Ardon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And when Azubah died, Caleb married Ephrathah, and she bore Hur to
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Hur fathered Uri, and Uri fathered Bezalel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And afterward Hezron went in to the daughter of Makir the father
        of Gilead. And he married her when he was sixty years old. And she bore Segub
        to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Segub fathered Jair, and he had twenty-three cities in the land
        of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Geshur and Aram took Havvoth-Jair from them, Kenath and its villages,
        sixty cities. All these were the descendants of Makir, the father of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And after the death of Hezron in Caleb-Ephrathah, Abijah the wife
        of Hezron bore to him Ashhur, the father of Tekoa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And the sons of Jerahmeel the firstborn of Hezron were Ram his firstborn,
        Bunah, Oren, Ozem, and Ahijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Jerahmeel had another wife, and her name was Atarah. She was
        the mother of Onam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The sons of Ram the firstborn of Jerahmeel were Maaz, Jamin, and
        Eker. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And the sons of Onam were Shammai and Jada. And the sons of Shammai
        were Nadab and Abishur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the name of the wife of Abishur was Abihail, and she bore to
        him Ahban and Molid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the sons of Nadab were Seled and Appaim. And Seled died without
        children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And the sons of Appaim: Ishi. The sons of Ishi: Sheshan. The sons
        of Sheshan: Ahlai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the sons of Jada the brother of Shammai: Jether and Jonathan.
        And Jether died without children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the sons of Jonathan: Peleth and Zaza. These were the children
        of Jerahmeel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And Sheshan had no sons, only daughters, but Sheshan had an Egyptian
        slave, and his name was Jarha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So Sheshan gave his daughter to Jarha his slave for a wife, and she
        bore to him Attai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And Attai fathered Nathan, and Nathan fathered Zabad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And Zabad fathered Ephlal, and Ephlal fathered Obed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And Obed fathered Jehu, and Jehu fathered Azariah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And Azariah fathered Helez, and Helez fathered Eleasah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And Eleasah fathered Sismai, and Sismai fathered Shallum. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And Shallum fathered Jekamiah, and Jekamiah fathered Elishama. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And the sons of Caleb the brother of Jerahmeel were Mesha his firstborn;
        he was the father of Ziph. The sons of Mareshah: Hebron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And the sons of Hebron were Korah, Tappuah, Rekem, and Shema. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And Shema fathered Raham, the father of Jorkeam. And Rekem fathered
        Shammai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And the son of Shammai was Maon, and Maon was the father of Beth-Zur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'And Ephah, the concubine of Caleb, gave birth to Haran, Moza, and
        Gazez. And Haran fathered Gazez. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And the sons of Jahdai were Regem, Jotham, Geshan, Pelet, Ephah,
        and Shaaph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Maacah, the concubine of Caleb, gave birth to Sheber and Tirhanah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'She also gave birth to Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheva the
        father of Machbenah and the father of Gibea; and the daughter of Caleb was
        Acsah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'These were the descendants of Caleb. The sons of Hur the firstborn
        of Ephrathah: Shobal the father of Kiriath-Jearim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Salma the father of Bethlehem, and Hareph the father of Beth-Gader. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'And Shobal the father of Kiriath-Jearim had other sons: Haroeh, half
        of the Menuhoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'And the families of Kiriath-Jearim: the Ithrites, the Puthites, the
        Shumathites, and the Mishraites. From these descended the Zorathites and
        the Eshtaolites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'The sons of Salma: Bethlehem, the Netophathites, Ataroth-Beth-Joab,
        and half of the Manahathites, the Zorites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'And the families of the scribes who lived at Jabez: the Tirathites,
        the Shimeathites, and the Sucathites. These were the Kenites who came from
        Hammath, the father of the house of Recab. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Descendants of David'
      title: The Descendants of David
      number: 1
      content: 'These were the sons of David who were born to him in Hebron: the
        firstborn, Amnon, by Ahinoam the Jezreelite; the second, Daniel, by Abigail
        the Carmelite; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'the third, Absalom, the son of Maacah the daughter of Talmai, king
        of Geshur; the fourth, Adonijah, the son of Haggith; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the fifth, Shephatiah, by Abital; the sixth, Ithream, by his wife
        Eglah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Six were born to him in Hebron. And he reigned there seven years
        and six months. And he reigned thirty-three years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And these were born to him in Jerusalem: Shimea, Shobab, Nathan,
        and Solomon, four by Bathshua the daughter of Ammiel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'then Ibhar, Elishama, Eliphelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet, nine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All these were the sons of David, besides the sons of the concubines.
        And Tamar was their sister. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the son of Solomon was Rehoboam; Abijah was his son, Asa was
        his son, Jehoshaphat was his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Joram was his son, Ahaziah was his son, Joash was his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Amaziah was his son, Azariah was his son, Jotham was his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ahaz was his son, Hezekiah was his son, Manasseh was his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Amon was his son, Josiah was his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the sons of Josiah: Johanan the firstborn, the second Jehoiakim,
        the third Zedekiah, the fourth Shallum. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the descendants of Jehoiakim: Jeconiah his son, Zedekiah his
        son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the sons of Jeconiah, the captive: Shealtiel his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Malchiram, Pedaiah, Shenazzar, Jekamiah, Hoshama, and Nedabiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the sons of Pedaiah: Zerubbabel and Shimei. And the sons of Zerubbabel:
        Meshullam and Hananiah, and Shelomith their sister, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and Hashubah, Ohel, Berekiah, Hasadiah, and Jushab-Hesed, five. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the sons of Hananiah: Pelatiah and Jeshaiah. The sons of Rephaiah,
        the sons of Arnan, the sons of Obadiah, the sons of Shecaniah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the sons of Shecaniah: Shemaiah. And the sons of Shemaiah: Hattush,
        Igal, Bariah, Neariah, and Shaphat, six. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the sons of Neariah: Elioenai, Hezekiah, and Azrikam, three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the sons of Elioenai: Hodaviah, Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan,
        Delaiah, and Anani, seven. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Descendants of David'
      title: The Descendants of David
      number: 1
      content: 'The sons of Judah: Perez, Hezron, Carmi, Hur, and Shobal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Reaiah the son of Shobal fathered Jahath, and Jahath fathered
        Ahumai and Lahad. These were the clans of the Zorathites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And these were the sons of Etam: Jezreel, Ishma, and Idbash. And
        the name of their sister was Hazzelelponi, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and Penuel was the father of Gedor, and Ezer was the father of Hushah.
        These were the sons of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah, the father of Bethlehem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Ashhur, the father of Tekoa, had two wives: Helah and Naarah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Naarah bore him Ahuzzam, Hepher, Temeni, and Haahashtari. These
        were the sons of Naarah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Helah: Zereth, Izhar, and Ethnan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Koz fathered Anub, Zobebah, and the clans of Aharhel, the son
        of Harum. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Jabez was more honorable than his brothers. And his mother called
        his name Jabez, saying, \u201CBecause I bore him in pain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Jabez called upon the God of Israel, saying, \u201COh that you
        would surely bless me and enlarge my border. And may your hand be with me,
        that you would keep me from evil so that it might not harm me!\u201D And
        God granted what he asked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Chelub, the brother of Shuhah, fathered Mehir. He was the father
        of Eshton. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Eshton fathered Beth-Rapha, Paseah, and Tehinnah, the father
        of the city of Nahash. These are the men of Recah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Kenaz: Othniel and Seraiah. And the sons of Othniel:
        Hathath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Meonothai fathered Ophrah; and Seraiah fathered Joab, the father
        of Ge-Harashim, because they were craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sons of Caleb, the son of Jephunneh: Iru, Elah, and Naam. And
        the sons of Elah: Kenaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Jehallelel: Ziph, Ziphah, Tiria, and Asarel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Ezrah: Jether, Mered, Epher, and Jalon. And she became
        pregnant with Miriam, Shammai, and Ishbah, the father of Eshtemoa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And his Judahite wife bore Jered the father of Gedor, Heber the father
        of Soco, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah. And these were the sons of Bithiah
        daughter of Pharaoh, whom Mered married. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of the wife of Hodiah, the sister of Naham, were the fathers
        of Keilah the Garmite and Eshtemoa the Maacathite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The sons of Shimon: Amnon, Rinnah, Ben-Hanan, and Tolon. The sons
        of Ishi: Zoheth and Ben-Zoheth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Shelah, the son of Judah: Er the father of Lecah, Laadah
        the father of Mareshah, and the families of the house of linen workers at
        Beth Ashbea; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and Jokim, and the men of Cozeba, and Joash, and Saraph, who ruled
        in Moab and returned to Lehem. (Now the records are ancient). '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Descendants of Simeon'
      title: Descendants of Simeon
      number: 23
      content: 'These were the potters and inhabitants of Netaim and Gederah. They
        lived there with the king in his service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Simeon: Nemuel, Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, Shaul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Shallum his son, Mibsam his son, Mishma his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The sons of Mishma: Hammuel his son, Zaccur his son, Shimei his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters, but his brothers did not
        have many children. But all their families did not multiply like the men
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And they lived in Beersheba, Moladah, Hazar Shual, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Bilhah, Ezem, Tolad, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Bethuel, Hormah, Ziklag, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Beth-Marcaboth, Hazar-Susim, Beth-Biri, and Shaaraim. These were
        their cities until David reigned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And their villages were Etam, Ain, Rimmon, Token, and Ashan, five
        cities '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'and all their villages that surrounding these cities as far as Baal.
        These were their settlements, and they kept a genealogical record for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Meshobab, Jamlech, and Joshah the son of Amaziah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Joel, and Jehu the son of Joshibiah, son of Seraiah, son of Asiel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And Elioenai, Jaakobah, Jeshohaiah, Asaiah, Adiel, Jesimiel, Benaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'and Ziza the son of Shiphi, son of Allon, son of Jedaiah, son of
        Shimri, son of Shemaiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "These mentioned by name were leaders in their families, and their
        fathers\u2019 households increased greatly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And they went to the entrance of Gedor, up to the east side of the
        valley, to seek pasture for their flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And they found fertile and good pasture, and the land was very broad,
        quiet, and at ease, for the former inhabitants there were from Ham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'These, mentioned by name, came in the days of Hezekiah, king of Judah,
        and attacked their tents and the Meunites who were found there. And they
        devoted them to destruction to this day, and they settled among them because
        there was pasture there for their flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And some of them from the Simeonites went to Mount Seir, five hundred
        men. And Pelatiah, Neariah, Rephaiah, and Uzziel, the sons of Ishi, were
        under their leadership. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And they destroyed the remainder of the Amalekites who had escaped,
        and they have lived there to this day. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Descendants of Reuben'
      title: The Descendants of Reuben
      number: 1
      content: 'The sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel (for he was the firstborn,
        but when he defiled the couch of his father, his birthright was given to
        the sons of Joseph, the son of Israel, so that he was not enrolled in the
        genealogy as the firstborn, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'though Judah became strong among his brothers and a chief came from
        him, but the birthright belonged to Joseph). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel: Enoch, Pallu, Hezron,
        and Carmi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sons of Joel: Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Micah his son, Reaiah his son, Baal his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Beerah his son, a leader of the Reubenites, whom Tiglath-Pilneser
        king of Assyria deported into exile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And his kinsmen by their families, when their generations were recorded
        in the genealogy: the chief, Jeiel, and Zechariah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and Bela son of Azaz, son of Shema, son of Joel, who lived in Aroer,
        as far as Nebo and Baal-Meon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He also lived to the east up to the entrance of the desert this side
        of the River Euphrates, for their livestock had multiplied in the land of
        Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Descendants of Gad'
      title: The Descendants of Gad
      number: 10
      content: 'And in the days of Saul they made war against the Hagrites, and they
        fell into their hand. And they lived in their tents in all the region east
        of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the sons of Gad lived near to them in the land of Bashan as far
        as Salecah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Joel the chief, Shapham the second, Janai, and Shaphat in Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And their kinsmen according to their fathers\u2019 households: Michael,
        Meshullam, Sheba, Jorai, Jacan, Zia, and Eber, seven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'These were the sons of Abihail the son of Huri, son of Jaroah, son
        of Gilead, son of Michael, son of Jeshishai, son of Jahdo, son of Buz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Ahi son of Abdiel, son of Guni, was chief in their fathers\u2019
        households. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And they lived in Gilead, in Bashan, and in its towns, and in all
        the pasturelands of Sharon to their limits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'All of them were enrolled in the genealogy in the days of Jotham,
        king of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam, king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh had valiant
        men who carried a shield and a sword, and archers, and who were expert in
        war, forty-four thousand seven hundred and sixty for going out as an army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And they made war against the Hagrites, Jetur, Naphish, and Nodab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And they were helped against them, and the Hagrites and all who were
        with them were given into their hand, for they cried out to God in the battle,
        and he responded to their prayer because they trusted in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And they captured their livestock: fifty thousand of their camels;
        two hundred and fifty thousand sheep; two thousand donkeys; and one hundred
        thousand men alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Half-Tribe of Manasseh'
      title: The Half-Tribe of Manasseh
      number: 22
      content: 'For many were slain because the war was of God. And they lived under
        them until the exile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the sons of the half-tribe of Manasseh lived in the land from
        Bashan to Baal-Hermon, Senir, and Mount Hermon. They were numerous. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Now these were the heads of their fathers\u2019 households: Epher,
        Ishi, Eliel, Azriel, Jeremiah, Hodaviah, and Jahdiel, mighty men of strength,
        famous men, heads of their fathers\u2019 households. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But they transgressed against the God of their ancestors and prostituted
        themselves after the gods of the peoples of the land, whom God had destroyed
        before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul, king of Assyria,
        and the spirit of Tiglath-Pilneser, king of Assyria, and he took them into
        exile, namely, the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh.
        And he brought them to Halah, Habor, Hara, and the river Gozan, until this
        day. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '   The sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The children of Amram: Aaron, Moses, and Miriam. The sons of Aaron:
        Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Eleazar fathered Phinehas; Phinehas fathered Abishua; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Abishua fathered Bukki; Bukki fathered Uzzi; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Uzzi fathered Zerahiah; Zerahiah fathered Meraioth; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Meraioth fathered Amariah; Amariah fathered Ahitub; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ahitub fathered Zadok; Zadok fathered Ahimaaz; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ahimaaz fathered Azariah; Azariah fathered Johanan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and Johanan fathered Azariah. It was he who served as priest in the
        temple that Solomon built in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Azariah fathered Amariah; Amariah fathered Ahitub; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Ahitub fathered Zadok; Zadok fathered Shallum; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Shallum fathered Hilkiah; Hilkiah fathered Azariah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Azariah fathered Seraiah; Seraiah fathered Jehozadak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Descendants of Levi'
      title: The Descendants of Levi
      number: 15
      content: 'And Jehozadak went into exile when Yahweh sent Judah and Jerusalem
        into exile by the hand of Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Levi: Gershom, Kohath, and Merari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now these are the names of the sons of Gershom: Libni and Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. Now these are the families of
        the Levites according to their ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Of Gershom: Libni his son, Jahath his son, Zimmah his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Joah his son, Iddo his son, Zerah his son, Jeatherai his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Kohath: Amminadab his son, Korah his son, Assir his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Elkanah his son, Ebiasaph his son, Assir his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Tahath his son, Uriel his son, Uzziah his son, and Shaul his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The sons of Elkanah: Amasai and Ahimoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Elkanah his son, Zophai his son, Nahath his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Eliab his son, Jeroham his son, Elkanah his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Samuel: Joel his firstborn and Abijah the second. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli, Libni his son, Shimei his son, Uzzah his
        son, '
      comments: []
    - name: "30: David\u2019s Appointees for Music in the Temple"
      title: "David\u2019s Appointees for Music in the Temple"
      number: 30
      content: 'Shimea his son, Haggiah his son, and Asaiah his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now these are the men whom David appointed for control of singing
        in the house of Yahweh where the ark rested. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'They were ministering with song before the tabernacle of the tent
        of assembly until Solomon built the temple of Yahweh in Jerusalem. And they
        stood according to their order with respect to their duty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now these are those who served and their sons. Of the sons of the
        Kohathites: Heman the singer, the son of Joel, son of Samuel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'son of Elkanah, son of Jeroham, son of Eliel, son of Toah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'son of Zuph, son of Elkanah, son of Mahath, son of Amasai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'son of Elkanah, son of Joel, son of Azariah, son of Zephaniah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'son of Tahath, son of Assir, son of Ebiasaph, son of Korah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'son of Izhar, son of Kohath, son of Levi, son of Israel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and his brother Asaph, who stood on his right namely, Asaph the son
        of Berechiah, son of Shimea, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'son of Michael, son of Baaseiah, son of Malkijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'son of Ethni, son of Zerah, son of Adaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'son of Ethan, son of Zimmah, son of Shimei, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'son of Jahath, son of Gershom, son of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'On the left were their brothers, the sons of Merari: Ethan the son
        of Kishi, son of Abdi, son of Malluch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'son of Hashabiah, son of Amaziah, son of Hilkiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'son of Amzi, son of Bani, son of Shemer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'son of Mahli, son of Mushi, son of Merari, son of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And their brothers the Levites were appointed for all the service
        of the tabernacle of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: The Descendants of Aaron'
      title: The Descendants of Aaron
      number: 49
      content: 'But Aaron and his sons made offerings on the altar of burnt offering
        and on the altar of incense for all the work of the most holy place, and
        to make atonement for Israel, according to all that Moses the servant of
        God had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Now these are the sons of Aaron: Eleazar his son, Phinehas his son,
        Abishua his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Bukki his son, Uzzi his son, Zerahiah his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Meraioth his son, Amariah his son, Ahitub his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Zadok his son, Ahimaaz his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'And these are their dwellings according to their settlements within
        their borders: to the sons of Aaron of the clans of Kohathites, for the first
        lot was theirs, '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'and they gave to them Hebron in the land of Judah and its surrounding
        pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'but the fields of the city and its villages they gave to Caleb the
        son of Jephunneh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'To the sons of Aaron they gave the cities of refuge: Hebron, Libnah
        with its pasturelands, Jattir, Eshtemoa with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'Hilen with its pasturelands, Debir with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Ashan with its pasturelands, and Beth-Shemesh with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'And from the tribe of Benjamin, Geba with its pasturelands, Alemeth
        with its pasturelands, and Anathoth with its pasturelands. All their cities
        were thirteen cities throughout their clans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'To the Kohathites who remained from the family of the half-tribe,
        the half of Manasseh, were given by lot ten cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'To the Gershomites according to their clans thirteen cities were
        allotted out of the tribe of Issachar, out of the tribe of Asher, out of
        the tribe of Naphtali, and out of the tribe of Manasseh in Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'To the Merarites twelve cities were allotted according to their clans
        out of the tribe of Reuben, out of the tribe of Gad, and out of the tribe
        of Zebulun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'So the Israelites gave the Levites the cities with their pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'And they gave by lot out of the tribe of Judah, out of the tribe
        of Simeon, and out of the tribe of Benjamin these cities that are mentioned
        by name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'And of the clans of the sons of Kohath were cities of their territory
        out of the tribe of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: 'And they gave them the cities of refuge: Shechem with its pasturelands
        in the hill country of Ephraim, Gezer with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: 'Jokmeam with its pasturelands, Beth-Horon with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: 'Aijalon with its pasturelands, and Gath-Rimmon with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: 'And out of the half-tribe of Manasseh: Aner with its pasturelands,
        and Bileam with its pasturelands for the remaining the clans of the Kohathites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: 'To the Gershomites were given out of the clan of the half-tribe of
        Manasseh: Golan in Bashan with its pasturelands and Ashtaroth with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: 'And out of the tribe of Issachar: Kedesh with its pasturelands, Daberath
        with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '73: '
      title: 
      number: 73
      content: 'Ramoth with its pasturelands, and Anem with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '74: '
      title: 
      number: 74
      content: 'And out of the tribe of Asher: Mashal with its pasturelands, Abdon
        with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '75: '
      title: 
      number: 75
      content: 'Hukok with its pasturelands, and Rehob with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '76: '
      title: 
      number: 76
      content: 'And out of the tribe of Naphtali: Kedesh in Galilee with its pasturelands,
        Hammon with its pasturelands, and Kiriathaim with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '77: '
      title: 
      number: 77
      content: 'To the remainder of the Merarites were allotted out of the tribe
        of Zebulun: Rimmono with its pasturelands, Tabor with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '78: '
      title: 
      number: 78
      content: 'And beyond the Jordan at Jericho, on the east side of the Jordan,
        out of the tribe of Reuben: Bezer in the wilderness with its pasturelands,
        Jahzah with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '79: '
      title: 
      number: 79
      content: 'Kedemoth with its pasturelands, and Mephaath with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '80: '
      title: 
      number: 80
      content: 'And out of the tribe of Gad: Ramoth in Gilead with its pasturelands,
        Mahanaim with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '81: '
      title: 
      number: 81
      content: 'Heshbon with its pasturelands, and Jazer with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Descendants of Issachar'
      title: The Descendants of Issachar
      number: 1
      content: 'The sons of Issachar: Tola, Puah, Jashub, and Shimron, four. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The sons of Tola: Uzzi, Rephaiah, Jeriel, Jahmai, Ibsam, and Shemuel,
        heads of their fathers\u2019 houses; for Tola, mighty warriors of their generations,
        their number in the days of David were twenty-two thousand six hundred. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sons of Uzzi: Izrahiah. And the sons of Izrahiah: Michael, Obadiah,
        Joel, and Isshiah; all five of them were chiefs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And in addition to them, according to their generations, according
        to the house of their fathers, were troops of the army for war: thirty-six
        thousand. For they had many wives and sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Descendants of Benjamin'
      title: The Descendants of Benjamin
      number: 5
      content: 'Now their kinsmen belonging to all the clans of Issachar were in
        all eighty-seven thousand mighty warriors, enrolled according to their genealogy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sons of Benjamin: Bela, Beker, and Jediael, three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Bela: Ezbon, Uzzi, Uzziel, Jerimoth, and Iri, five, the
        heads of the house of the fathers, mighty warriors. And their enrollment
        by genealogy was twenty-two thousand thirty-four. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The sons of Beker: Zemirah, Joash, Eliezer, Elioenai, Omri, Jeremoth,
        Abijah, Anathoth, and Alemeth. All these were the sons of Beker. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And their enrollment by genealogy according to their generations,
        as heads of the house of their fathers, mighty warriors, was twenty thousand
        two hundred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The sons of Jediael: Bilhan. And the sons of Bilhan: Jeush, Benjamin,
        Ehud, Kenaanah, Zethan, Tarshish, and Ahishahar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'All these were the sons of Jediael according to the heads of the
        families, mighty warriors, seventeen thousand two hundred, able to go to
        war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Descendants of Naphtali'
      title: The Descendants of Naphtali
      number: 12
      content: 'And Shuppim and Huppim were the sons of Ir; Hushim, the son of Aher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Descendants of Manasseh'
      title: The Descendants of Manasseh
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Naphtali: Jahziel, Guni, Jezer, and Shallum, the descendants
        of Bilhah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The sons of Manasseh: Asriel, whom his Aramean concubine bore; she
        gave birth to Makir the father of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Machir took a wife for Huppim and for Shuppim. And the name of
        his sister was Maacah. And the name of the second, Zelophehad. And Zelophehad
        had daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Maacah the wife of Machir gave birth to a son, and she called
        his name Peresh. And the name of his brother was Sheresh, and his sons were
        Ulam and Rekem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Ulam: Bedan. These were the sons of Gilead the son of
        Makir, son of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And his sister, Hammolecheth, gave birth to Ishhod, Abiezer, and
        Mahlah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Descendants of Ephraim'
      title: The Descendants of Ephraim
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Shemida were Ahian, Shechem, Likhi, and Aniam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The sons of Ephraim: Shuthelah and Bered his son, Tahath his son,
        Eleadah his son, Tahath his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Zabad his son, Shuthelah his son, and Ezer and Elead. And the men
        of Gath who were born in the land killed them because they came down to take
        their livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Ephraim their father mourned many days, and his brothers came
        to comfort him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Ephraim went in to his wife, and she conceived and gave birth
        to a son. And he called his name Beriah because disaster had been upon his
        house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And his daughter was Sheerah, and she built Lower and Upper Beth-Horon
        and Uzzen-Sheerah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Rephah was his son, and Resheph, and Telah his son, Tahan his
        son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Ladan his son, Ammihud his son, Elishama his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Nun his son, Joshua his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And their property and their dwellings were Bethel and its towns.
        And to the east, Naaran. And to the west, Gezer and its towns, and Shechem
        and its towns, up to Aija and its towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: The Descendants of Asher'
      title: The Descendants of Asher
      number: 29
      content: 'And along the borders of the sons of Manasseh: Beth-Shean and its
        towns, Taanach and its towns, Megiddo and its towns, and Dor and its towns.
        In these lived the sons of Joseph the son of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The sons of Asher: Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, Beriah, and their sister
        Serah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The sons of Beriah: Heber and Malkiel, who was the father of Birzayith.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And Heber fathered Japhlet, Shomer, Hotham, and their sister Shua. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The sons of Japhlet: Pasach, Bimhal, and Ashvath. These were the
        sons of Japhlet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The sons of Shemer: Ahi, Rohgah, Jehubbah, and Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The sons of Helem his brother: Zophah, Imna, Shelesh, and Amal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The sons of Zophah: Suah, Harnepher, Shual, Beri, Imrah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Bezer, Hod, Shamma, Shilshah, Ithran, and Beera. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The sons of Jether: Jephunneh, Pispah, and Ara. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The sons of Ulla: Arah, Hanniel, and Rizia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'All of these were the sons of Asher, heads of the house of the fathers,
        chosen mighty warriors, heads of the princes. And their number enrolled by
        genealogy, in the army for the war, was twenty-six thousand men. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Genealogy of Saul'
      title: The Genealogy of Saul
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Benjamin fathered Bela his firstborn, Ashbel the second, Aharah
        the third, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Nohah the fourth, and Rapha the fifth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Bela had sons: Addar, Gera, Abihud, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Abishua, Naaman, Ahoah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Gera, Shephuphan, and Huram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And these are the sons of Ehud (these were heads of the families
        for the inhabitants of Geba, and they took them away to Manahath): '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Naaman, Ahijah, and Gera, who took them away. And he fathered Uzza
        and Ahihud. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Shaharaim fathered children in the fields of Moab after he had
        sent them away\u2014Hushim and Baara, his wives. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And he fathered by Hodesh his wife Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malcam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Jeuz, Sakia, and Mirmah. These were his sons, heads of the families.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And by Husham he fathered Abitub and Elpaal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Elpaal: Eber, Misham, Shemed (he built Ono and Lod with
        its towns),  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and Beriah and Shema who were the heads of the families of the inhabitants
        of Aijalon (they themselves chased away the inhabitants of Gath). '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now Ahio, Shashak, Jeremoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Zebadiah, Arad, Eder, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Michael, Ishpah, and Joha were sons of Beriah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Ishmerai, Izliah, and Jobab were the sons of Elpaal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Jakim, Zikri, Zabdi, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Adaiah, Beraiah, and Shimrath were the sons of Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Ishpan, Eber, Eliel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Abdon, Zikri, Hanan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Hananiah, Elam, Antothijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Iphdeiah, and Peniel were the sons of Shashak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Jaareshiah, Elijah, and Zikri were the sons of Jeroham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'These were the heads of the families according to their generations,
        chiefs. These lived in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And Jeiel the father of Gibeon lived in Gibeon. And the name of his
        wife was Maacah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And his firstborn son was Abdon, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Nadab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Gedor, Ahio, Zeker, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'and Mikloth (he fathered Shimeah). Now these also lived nearby their
        brothers in Jerusalem with their kinsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And Ner fathered Kish, and Kish fathered Saul, and Saul fathered
        Jonathan, Malchi-Shua, Abinadab, and Eshbaal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And the son of Jonathan was Merib-baal, and Merib-baal fathered Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the sons of Micah: Pithon, Melech, Tarea, and Ahaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And Ahaz fathered Jehoaddah, and Jehoaddah fathered Alemeth, Azmaveth,
        and Zimri. And Zimri fathered Moza. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And Moza fathered Binea; Raphah was his son, Eleasah his son, and
        Azel his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And Azel had six sons, and these are their names: Azrikam, Bokeru,
        Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. All these were the sons of Azel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And the sons of Eshek his brother: Ulam his firstborn, Jeush the
        second, and Eliphelet the third. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And the sons of Ulam were men who were mighty warriors, bowmen, and
        they had many sons and grandsons, one hundred and fifty. All these were Benjaminites. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Genealogy of Returned Exiles'
      title: The Genealogy of Returned Exiles
      number: 1
      content: 'So all Israel was enrolled in genealogy. And behold, they were written
        in the book of the kings of Israel. And Judah was taken away to Babylon on
        account of their sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now the first inhabitants who were settled on their property in their
        cities in Israel were the priests, the Levites, and the temple servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And some of the people of Judah, Benjamin, Ephraim, and Manasseh
        lived in Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Uthai the son of Ammihud, son of Omri, son of Imri, son of Bani,
        from the sons of Perez, the son of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And from the Shilonites: Asaiah the firstborn and his sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And from the sons of Zerah: Jeuel and their brethren, six hundred
        and ninety. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And from the sons of Benjamin: Sallu the son of Meshullam, son of
        Hodaviah, the son of Hassenuah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ibneah the son of Jeroham; Elah the son of Uzzi, son of Michri; Meshullam
        the son of Shephatiah, son of Reuel, son of Ibnijah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and their brethren according to their generations, nine hundred and
        fifty-six. All these men were the heads of the families in the house of their
        fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And from the priests: Jedaiah; Jehoiarib; Jakin; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Azariah son of Hilkiah, son of Meshullam, son of Zadok, son of Meraioth,
        son of Ahitub, the commander of the house of God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Adaiah son of Jeroham, son of Pashhur, son of Malkijah; Maasai the
        son of Adiel, son of Jahzerah, son of Meshullam, son of Meshillemith, son
        of Immer; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and their kinsmen, heads of the house of their fathers, one thousand
        seven hundred and sixty mighty men for the work of the service of the house
        of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And from the Levites: Shemaiah son of Hasshub, son of Azrikam, son
        of Hashabiah, from the sons of Merari; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Bakbakkar; Heresh; Galal; Mattaniah the son of Mica, son of Zicri,
        son of Asaph; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Obadiah the son of Shemaiah, son of Galal, son of Jeduthun; and Berechiah
        the son of Asa, son of Elkanah, who lived in the villages of Netophathite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the gatekeepers were Shallum, Akkub, Talmon, Ahiman, and their
        brethren (Shallum was the chief); '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'until then they were gatekeepers at the gate of the king on the east
        side toward the camps of the Levites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Shallum the son of Kore, son of Ebiasaph, son of Korah, and his
        kinsmen of the house of his fathers, the Korahites, were over the work of
        the service, the guardians of the entrances to the tent, and their fathers
        were over the camp of Yahweh, guardians of the entrance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Phinehas the son of Eleazar was the leader over them in time
        past; Yahweh was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Zechariah the son of Meshelemiah was gatekeeper at the doorway to
        the tent of assembly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'All of them were chosen as gatekeepers at the entrances, two hundred
        and twelve. They were enrolled by genealogies in their villages. They were
        established by David and Samuel the seer on account of their faithfulness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So they and their sons were over the gates of the house of Yahweh
        at the house of the tent as guards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The gatekeepers were on four sides: east, west, north, and south. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And their brethren in their villages were to come every seven days
        by turn to be with these. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For the four mighty gatekeepers, they who were Levites, were entrusted
        and were over the chambers and over the storerooms of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And they lodged all around the house of God, for upon them was a
        responsibility. And they had charge of opening the house of God every morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And some of them were over the utensils of the service, for they
        count them when they are brought in and they count them when they are brought
        out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And some of them were appointed over the objects, over the objects
        of the sanctuary, and over the wheat flour and the wine, the olive oil, the
        frankincense, and the spices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And some of the sons of the priests mixed the fragrant ointment for
        the spices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And Mattithiah, one of the Levites, was the firstborn of Shallum
        the Korahite and was entrusted with the work of the pan breads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And from the sons of the Kohathites, some of their kinsmen were over
        the showbread to prepare it every Sabbath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Now these were the singers; the heads of the families of the Levites
        were in the chambers free from other service, for day and night they were
        over them on the service. '
      comments: []
    - name: "34: Saul\u2019s Genealogy Repeated"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Genealogy Repeated"
      number: 34
      content: 'These were the heads of the families of the Levites according to
        their genealogies, leaders. These lived in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And these lived in Gibeon: Jeiel the father of Gibeon. And the name
        of his wife was Maacah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And his firstborn son Abdon, and Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Gedor, Ahio, Zechariah, and Mikloth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And Mikloth fathered Shimeam. And they also lived nearby their brothers
        in Jerusalem with their brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And Ner fathered Kish, and Kish fathered Saul, and Saul fathered
        Jonathan, Malchi-Shua, Abinadab, and Eshbaal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And the son of Jonathan was Meribaal. And Meribaal fathered Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And the sons of Micah were Pithon, Melech, Tahrea, and Ahaz.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And Ahaz fathered Jarah, and Jarah fathered Alemeth, Azmaveth, and
        Zimri. And Zimri fathered Moza, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'and Moza fathered Binea; and Rephaiah was his son, Eleasah his son,
        Azel his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And Azel had six sons, and these are their names: Azrikam, Bokeru,
        Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. These were the sons of Azel. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death of Saul and His Sons'
      title: The Death of Saul and His Sons
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the Philistines fought against Israel, and every Israelite fled
        away from before the Philistines. And they fell slain upon Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the Philistines overtook Saul and his sons. And the Philistines
        killed Jonathan, Abinadab, and Malki-Shua, the sons of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the battle was heavy against Saul, and the archers found him,
        and he was wounded by the archers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Saul said to his armor-bearer, \u201CDraw your sword and thrust
        me through with it, lest these uncircumcised come and deal harshly with me.\u201D
        But he was very afraid. Then Saul took the sword and fell upon it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When his armor-bearer saw that Saul was dead, he also fell upon the
        sword, and he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Saul died. And his three sons and all his house died together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when all the men of Israel who were in the valley saw that they
        had fled and that Saul and his sons were dead, they abandoned their cities
        and fled. Then the Philistines came and dwelled in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And it happened that on the next day when the Philistines came to
        strip the dead, they found Saul and his sons fallen on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they stripped him and took his head and his weapons, and they
        sent them throughout the land of the Philistines to bring news to their idols
        and the nation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And they put his weapons in the temple of their gods, and they fastened
        his skull to the temple of Dagon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When all Jabesh-Gilead heard all that the Philistines had done to
        Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'every strong man arose and took the dead body of Saul and the dead
        bodies of his sons and brought them to Jabesh. And they buried their bones
        under the oak in Jabesh and fasted seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Saul died on account of his sin which he had sinned against Yahweh
        concerning the command of Yahweh that he did not keep. He also consulted
        a medium to seek guidance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But he did not seek Yahweh. So Yahweh put him to death and turned
        over the kingship to David, the son of Jesse. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Anointing of David as King'
      title: The Anointing of David as King
      number: 1
      content: "Then all Israel gathered to David in Hebron, saying, \u201CLook\u2014we
        are your flesh and bones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For some time now, even when Saul was king, you were the one who
        led the army of Israel in battle. And Yahweh your God said to you, \u2018You
        will shepherd my people Israel and will be leader over my people Israel.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, and David
        made a covenant with them at Hebron in the presence of Yahweh. And they anointed
        David as king over Israel according to the word of Yahweh by the hand of
        Samuel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And David and all Israel went to Jerusalem (that is Jebus). And the
        Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land, were there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the inhabitants of Jebus said to David, \u201CYou will not enter
        here.\u201D But David captured the stronghold of Zion; that is, the city
        of David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then David said, \u201CWhoever strikes the Jebusites first will be
        chief and commander.\u201D And Joab the son of Zeruiah went up first and
        became chief. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And David lived in the fortress. Therefore they called it the city
        of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he built the city all around from the Millo and up to the circuit.
        And Joab restored the remainder of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: David\u2019s Mighty Men"
      title: "David\u2019s Mighty Men"
      number: 9
      content: 'And David became greater and greater. And Yahweh of hosts was with
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now these are the chiefs of the mighty men who were for David, who
        gave him strong support in his kingdom, together with all Israel to make
        him king according to the word of Yahweh concerning Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And this is the numbering of the mighty warriors who were for David:
        Jashobeam son of Hachmoni was chief of the three. He himself raised his spear
        against three hundred whom he killed on one occasion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And after him was Eleazar son of Dodo the Ahohite. He was among the
        three mighty warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He himself was with David at Pas-Dammim when the Philistines were
        gathered there for the battle. And there was a plot of the field filled with
        barley, and the people fled before the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But they took their stand in the middle of the plot and defended
        it. And they killed the Philistines. And Yahweh saved them with a great victory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And three of the thirty chiefs went down toward the rock to David
        at the cave of Adullam when the army of the Philistines was encamped in the
        valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And David was then in the stronghold, and the garrison of the Philistines
        was then in Bethlehem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And David had a craving, and he said, \u201CWho could give me a drink
        of water from the well of Bethlehem that is by the gate!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the three broke through into the camp of the Philistines and
        drew water from the well of Bethlehem that was by the gate and brought it
        and came to David. But David would not drink it and poured it out before
        Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he said, \u201CFar be it from me that I would do this before
        my God. Shall I drink the lifeblood of these men? For at the risk of their
        lives they brought it.\u201D And he was not willing to drink it. These things
        the three mighty men did. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now Abishai the brother of Joab was himself the head of the three.
        And he roused himself with his spear against three hundred whom he killed
        and made a name for himself among the three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He was twice as renowned among the three and was their commander.
        But he did not attain to the three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was a strong man from Kabzeel, one
        who did great deeds. He himself struck down two sons of Ariel of Moab. And
        he himself went down and struck down a lion within a pit on a snowy day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he himself struck down an Egyptian man, a large man five cubits
        tall. And in the hand of the Egyptian was a spear like a weaver\u2019s beam.
        But he went down to him with a club and seized the spear from the hand of
        the Egyptian and killed him with his own spear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'These things Benaiah son of Jehoiada did and had a name among the
        three mighty warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He himself was certainly distinguished among the thirty, but he did
        not attain to the three. And David appointed him over his bodyguard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the mighty warriors of the troops were Asahel the brother of
        Joab, Elhanan the son of Dodo from Bethlehem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Shammoth the Harorite, Helez the Pelonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite, Abiezer the Anathothite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Sibbecai the Hushathite, Ilai the Ahohite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Maharai the Netophathite, Heled the son of Baanah the Netophathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Ittai the son of Ribai from Gibeah of the people of Benjamin, Benaiah
        the Pirathonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Hurai of the valleys of Gaash, Abiel the Arbathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Azmaveth the Baharumite, Eliahba the Shaalbonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'the sons of Hashem the Gizonite, Jehonathan the son of Shagee the
        Hararite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Ahiam the son of Sacar the Hararite, Eliphal the son of Ur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Hepher the Mekerathite, Ahijah the Pelonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Hezro the Carmelite, Naari the son of Ezbai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Joel the brother of Nathan, Mibhar the son of Hagri, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the Beerothite, the bearer of the weapons
        of Joab the son of Zeruiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Uriah the Hittite, Zabad the son of Ahlai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Adina the son of Shiza the Reubenite, a leader of the Reubenites,
        and thirty with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Hanan the son of Maacah, Jehoshaphat the Mithnite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Uzzia the Ashterathite, Shama and Jeiel the sons of Hotham the Aroerite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Jediael the son of Shimri and Joha his brother the Tizite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Eliel the Mahavite, Jeribai and Joshaviah the sons of Elnaam, Ithmah
        the Moabite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Eliel, Obed, and Jaasiel the Mezobaite. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David and His Mighty Men at Ziklag'
      title: David and His Mighty Men at Ziklag
      number: 1
      content: 'Now these are the ones who came to David at Ziklag while he was still
        shut up because of Saul, the son of Kish. And they were the mighty warriors
        helping with the war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They were armed with the bow, able to shoot right-handed or left-handed,
        slinging stones or shooting arrows with the bow; they were kinsmen of Saul
        from Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The leader was Ahiezer, then Jehoash, sons of Shemaah the Gibeonite;
        Jeiel and Pelet, sons of Azmaveth; Beracah; Jehu the Anathothite; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Ishmaiah the Gibeonite, a mighty warrior among the thirty who was
        over the thirty; Jeremiah; Jahaziel; Johanan; Jozabad the Gederathite; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: ' Eluzai; Jerimoth; Bealiah; Shemariah; Shephatiah the Hariphite; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Elkanah, Isshiah, Azarel, Joezer, and Jashobeam the Korahites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Joelah and Zebadiah, sons of Jeroham from the Gedor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And from the Gadites, valiant mighty warriors, soldiers fit for war,
        expert with shield and spear, defected to David at the fortress toward the
        wilderness. And they had faces like lions and were swift as gazelles upon
        the mountains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ezer the chief, Obadiah second, Eliab third, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Mishmannah fourth, Jeremiah fifth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Attai sixth, Eliel seventh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Jehonan eighth, Elzabad ninth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jeremiah tenth, Macbannai eleventh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'These were the sons of Gad, leaders of the army. The smallest one
        was as a hundred, and the greatest as a thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These were they who crossed the Jordan in the first month, when it
        was filled over its banks. And they put to flight all who were in the valley
        to the east and to the west. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And some of the sons of Benjamin and from Judah came to the fortress,
        to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And David went out to meet them and answered and said to them, \u201CIf
        you come in peace to me, to help me, my heart will be joined with you, but
        if you come to betray me to my adversaries, although there is no wrong on
        my hands, may the God of our fathers see and pass judgment.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the Spirit came upon Amasai, chief of the thirty who said: \u201CWe
        are yours, O David! And we are with you, O son of Jesse! Peace! Peace to
        you, and peace to those who help you, for your God helps you.\u201D So David
        appointed them as heads of the troops. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And some Manassites deserted to David when he came with the Philistines
        to the battle against Saul, but he did not help them, for the rulers of the
        Philistines sent him away upon counsel, saying, \u201CHe will desert to his
        master Saul at the cost of our heads.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When he went to Ziklag some Manassites deserted to him: Adnah, Jehozabad,
        Jediael, Michael, Jozabad, Elihu, and Zillethai, heads of the thousands that
        were for Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And they themselves helped David against the troops, for all of them
        were mighty men of strength and were commanders in the army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Day in and day out they came to David to help him until there was
        a great army, like the army of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And these are the numbers of the chiefs of those prepared for the
        army who came to David at Hebron to turn the kingdom of Saul over to him
        according to the word of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Judah bearing shield and spear: six thousand eight hundred
        armed troops. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'From the men of Simeon, mighty warriors of strength for war: seven
        thousand one hundred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'From the Levites: four thousand six hundred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Jehoiada the chief officer of the house of Aaron, and with him, three
        thousand seven hundred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And Zadok, a young man, a mighty warrior of strength, and the house
        of his father: twenty-two commanders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'From the men of Benjamin, kinsmen of Saul, three thousand, and even
        still the majority of them remained loyal to the house of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And from the men of Ephraim: twenty thousand eight hundred mighty
        warriors of strength, famous men in the house of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And from the half-tribe of Manasseh: eighteen thousand who were designated
        by name to come to make David king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And from the men of Issachar: men who were skilled in understanding
        the times to know what Israel should do. Their chiefs were two hundred, and
        all their kinsmen were under their command. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'From Zebulun, those who went out armed, equipped for battle with
        all the weapons of war: fifty thousand to help David with singleness of purpose.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'From Naphtali: one thousand commanders; and those with them with
        shield and spear: thirty-seven thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'From the Danites, those equipped for battle: twenty-eight thousand
        six hundred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And from Asher, those who went out armed and prepared for battle:
        forty thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And from beyond the Jordan, from the Reubenites and the Gadites and
        the half-tribe of Manasseh, with all their weapons of war for battle: one
        hundred and twenty thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'All these were men of war arrayed in battle line with a whole heart.
        They came to Hebron to make David king over all Israel. Likewise, all the
        rest of Israel had one heart to make David king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And they were there with David three days, eating and drinking, for
        their kinsmen were prepared for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And also their relatives, as far as Issachar and Zebulun and Naphtali,
        brought food on donkeys, on camels, on mules, and on oxen\u2014provisions
        of flour, cakes of figs, raisin cakes, wine and oil, cattle and sheep in
        abundance, for there was great joy in Israel. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark of the Covenant Brought from Kiriath-Jearim'
      title: The Ark of the Covenant Brought from Kiriath-Jearim
      number: 1
      content: 'And David consulted with the commanders of thousands and hundreds,
        with every leader. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And David said to all the assembly of Israel, \u201CIf it seems good
        to you and before Yahweh our God, let us send word abroad to our brothers
        who remain in all the land of Israel and to the priests and Levites with
        them in the cities with their pasturelands that they might be gathered to
        us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then let us bring around the ark of our God to us, for we did not
        seek it in the days of Saul.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And all the assembly agreed to do so, for the word was pleasing in
        the eyes of all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And David summoned all Israel from Shihor of Egypt up to Lebo-Hamath
        to bring the ark of God from Kiriath-Jearim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And David and all Israel went up to Baalah, Kiriath-Jearim of Judah,
        to bring up from there the ark of Yahweh God who is enthroned between the
        cherubim, which is called the name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And they carried the ark of God upon a new cart from the house of
        Abinadab, and Uzza and Ahio were driving the cart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now David and all Israel were celebrating before God with all their
        strength, and with songs, lyres, harps, tambourines, cymbals, and trumpets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when they came to the threshing floor of Kidon, Uzza reached
        out his hand to hold the ark because the cattle had stumbled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Yahweh was angry with Uzza, and he struck him down because he
        reached his hand upon the ark. And he died there before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And David was angry because Yahweh had broken out in wrath against
        Uzza. And that place is called Perez Uzza unto this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And David feared God on that day, saying, \u201CHow can I bring the
        ark of God home to me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So David did not move the ark to himself into the city of David but
        diverted it to the house of Obed-Edom the Gittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the ark of God remained with the household of Obed-Edom in his
        house three months. And Yahweh blessed the household of Obed-Edom and all
        that he had. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Wives and Children"
      title: "David\u2019s Wives and Children"
      number: 1
      content: 'And Hiram, king of Tyre, sent messengers to David and cedar trees,
        masons, and carpenters to build a house for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And David knew that Yahweh had established him as king over Israel
        and that his kingdom was highly exalted for the sake of his people Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And David took more wives in Jerusalem, and David fathered more sons
        and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now these are the names of the children who were born to him in Jerusalem:
        Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ibhar, Elishua, Elpelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: David Defeats the Philistines'
      title: David Defeats the Philistines
      number: 7
      content: 'Elishama, Beeliada, and Eliphelet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed as king over
        all Israel, all the Philistines went up to search for David. But David heard
        and went out from before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now the Philistines came and carried out a raid in the Valley of
        Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then David inquired of God, saying, \u201CShall I go up against the
        Philistines? Will you put them into my hand?\u201D And Yahweh said to him,
        \u201CGo up. I will put them into your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And he went up to Baal-Perazim, and David struck them there. And
        David said, \u201CGod has burst out against my enemies by my hand like waters
        burst out.\u201D Therefore they will call the name of this place Baal-Perazim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they abandoned their gods there. And David commanded, and they
        were burnt with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the Philistines carried out another raid in the valley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then David inquired again of God. And God said to him, \u201CYou
        shall not go up after them. Go around from before them and come against them
        the opposite way of the balsam trees. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And it shall be that when you hear the sound of marching in the tops
        of the balsam trees, then go out into battle, for God goes out before you
        to strike the camp of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And David did as God commanded him, and they struck the camp of the
        Philistines from Gibeon to Gezer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the fame of David went out through all the lands. And Yahweh
        put the fear of him upon all the nations. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Wives and Children"
      title: "David\u2019s Wives and Children"
      number: 1
      content: 'And David built houses for himself in the city of David, and he established
        a place for the ark of God. And he pitched a tent for it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then David ordered that none except the Levites should carry the
        ark of God, for Yahweh had chosen them to carry the ark of Yahweh and to
        serve him forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And David gathered all Israel to Jerusalem to bring up the ark of
        Yahweh to its place that he had established for it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And David gathered the sons of Aaron and the Levites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Of the sons of Kohath: Uriel the chief and one hundred and twenty
        of his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Of the sons of Merari: Asaiah the chief and two hundred and twenty
        of his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Of the sons of Gershom: Joel the chief and one hundred and thirty
        of his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Of the sons of Elizaphan: Shemaiah the chief and two hundred of his
        brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Of the sons of Hebron: Eliel the chief and eighty of his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Of the sons of Uzziel: Amminadab the chief and one hundred and twelve
        of his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then David summoned Zadok and Abiathar the priests, and the Levites
        Uriel, Asaiah, Joel, Shemaiah, Eliel, and Amminadab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CYou are the heads of the families for
        the Levites. Sanctify yourselves and your brothers and bring up the ark of
        Yahweh, the God of Israel, to the place I have established for it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Because the first time you did not, and Yahweh our God burst out
        against us, for we did not care for it according to the law.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the priests and the Levites sanctified themselves to bring up
        the ark of Yahweh, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the sons of the Levites carried the ark of God according to what
        Moses commanded, according to the word of Yahweh, on their shoulders with
        the carrying poles upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then David ordered the chiefs of the Levites to appoint their brothers
        as singers with instruments of song, musical instruments, stringed instruments,
        and cymbals, raising their voices for joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the Levites appointed Heman son of Joel, and from his brothers,
        Asaph the son of Berekiah, and from the sons of Merari, their brothers, Ethan
        the son of Kushaiah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and with them their brothers of the second rank, Zechariah the son,
        Jaaziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattithiah,
        Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, and the gatekeepers Obed-Edom and Jeiel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the singers, Heman, Asaph, and Ethan, were to sound bronze cymbals; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Zechariah, Aziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Maaseiah, and
        Benaiah were to play on harps according to Alamoth; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, Obed-Edom, Jeiel, and Azaziah
        were to play lyres, directing according to the Sheminith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Kenaniah, chief of the Levites in singing, was to be an instructor
        in singing because he understood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Berekiah and Elkanah were gatekeepers for the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Shebaniah, Jehoshaphat, Nethanel, Amasai, Zechariah, Benaiah,
        and Elizezer the priests sounded the trumpets before the ark of God. And
        Obed-Edom and Jehiah were gatekeepers for the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And it happened that David and the elders of Israel and the commanders
        of thousands went to bring up the ark of the covenant of Yahweh from the
        house of Obed-Edom with joy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And it happened that when God helped the Levites carrying the ark
        of the covenant of Yahweh, they sacrificed seven bulls and seven rams. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now David was clothed with a robe of fine linen; so also all the
        Levites who were carrying the ark, the singers, and Kenaniah the chief of
        the singing. And David wore a linen ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And all Israel brought up the ark of the covenant of Yahweh with
        shouting, with the sound of a shofar, and with trumpets and cymbals, making
        loud music with musical instruments and stringed instruments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And when the ark of the covenant of Yahweh came into the city of
        David, then Michal the daughter of Saul looked down from the window and saw
        the king, David, leaping and dancing. And she despised him in her heart. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark of the Covenant Placed in Its Tent'
      title: The Ark of the Covenant Placed in Its Tent
      number: 1
      content: 'And they brought the ark of God and set it inside the tent that David
        had pitched for it. And they offered burnt offerings and fellowship offerings
        before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when David had finished offering the burnt offerings and fellowship
        offerings, he blessed the people in the name of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he distributed to every man of Israel, both men and women, to
        each person a loaf of bread, a cake of dates, and a cake of raisins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then he appointed some of the Levites as ministers before the ark
        of Yahweh, to invoke, thank, and praise Yahweh the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Asaph was chief, and his second was Zechariah; Jeiel, Shemiramoth,
        Jehiel, Mattithiah, Eliab, Benaiah, Obed-Edom, and Jeiel were on harps and
        lyres. And Asaph played on the cymbals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Benaiah and Jahaziel the priests blew on the trumpets continually
        before the ark of the covenant of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: David\u2019s Song of Thanks"
      title: "David\u2019s Song of Thanks"
      number: 7
      content: 'Then on that day David first appointed to give thanks to Yahweh by
        the hand of Asaph and his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Give thanks to Yahweh; call upon his name; make known his deeds among
        the nations! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Sing to him; sing praises to him; tell of his wondrous works! '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Glory in his holy name; let the hearts of those seeking Yahweh rejoice! '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Seek Yahweh and his strength; seek his face continually! '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Remember his wonderful works that he has done, his wonders and the
        judgments of his mouth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'O offspring of Israel, his servant, O sons of Jacob, his chosen ones! '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He is Yahweh our God; his judgments are in all the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Remember his covenant forever, the word he commanded for a thousand
        generations, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'that he made with Abraham, his sworn oath to Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he confirmed it to Jacob as a statute, an everlasting covenant
        to Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "saying, \u201CTo you I will give the land of Canaan, the portion
        of your inheritance.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When you were few in number, little, and sojourners were in it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'when they wandered from nation to nation, and from one kingdom to
        another people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'he did not allow anyone to oppress them, and he rebuked kings on
        their account, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "saying, \u201CYou must not touch my anointed nor do harm to my prophets!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Sing to Yahweh, all the earth! Proclaim his salvation from day to
        day! '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Proclaim his glory among the nations, his wondrous works among the
        peoples! '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For Yahweh is great and greatly praised, and he is feared among all
        gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For all the gods of the nations are idols, but Yahweh made the heavens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Splendor and majesty are before him; strength and joy are in his
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Ascribe to Yahweh, O clans of the nations, ascribe to Yahweh glory
        and strength! '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Ascribe to Yahweh the glory of his name! Lift up an offering and
        come before him! Bow down to Yahweh in the splendor of holiness! '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Tremble before him, all the earth; surely the world shall not be
        shaken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Let the heavens rejoice, and let the earth be glad, and let them
        tell the peoples, \u201CYahweh reigns!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Let the sea roar and its fullness; let the field rejoice and all
        that is in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then the trees of the forest shall sing for joy before Yahweh, for
        he comes to judge the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Oh give thanks to Yahweh, for he is good; his loyal love is everlasting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then say, \u201CSave us, O God of our salvation; gather us and rescue
        us from the nations that we may give thanks to your holy name and glory in
        your praise. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Worship and the Ark'
      title: Worship and the Ark
      number: 36
      content: "Blessed be Yahweh the God of Israel, from everlasting to everlasting!\u201D
        Then all the people said, \u201CAmen!\u201D and praised Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So he left Asaph and his brothers there before the ark of the covenant
        of Yahweh to minister before the ark regularly as each day required,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'and he left Obed-Edom with his sixty-eight brothers. And Obed-Edom,
        the son of Jeduthun, and Hosah were gatekeepers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And he left Zadok the priest and his brothers the priests before
        the tabernacle of Yahweh at the high place which was at Gibeon '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'to offer burnt offerings regularly to Yahweh on the altar of burnt
        offering, morning and evening, according to all that was written in the law
        of Yahweh that he commanded concerning Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And with them were Heman and Jeduthun and the remainder of those
        chosen, who were designated by name to give thanks to Yahweh, for his loyal
        love is everlasting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And Heman and Jeduthun with them had trumpets and cymbals for making
        music, along with instruments for the song of God. And the sons of Jeduthun
        were at the gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Then all the people went each to his house, and David turned to bless
        his household. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Yahweh\u2019s Covenant with David"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Covenant with David"
      number: 1
      content: "And as David lived in his house, David said to Nathan the prophet,
        \u201CLook, I live in a house of cedar, but the ark of the covenant of Yahweh
        is under tent curtains.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Nathan said to David, \u201CWhatever is in your heart, do, for
        God is with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And it happened that same night the word of God came to Nathan, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CGo and say to David my servant, \u2018Thus says Yahweh, \u201CYou
        are not to build a house for me to live in, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'for I have not lived in a house from the day that I brought out Israel
        unto this day. I have been from tent to tent and from tabernacle to tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "In every place I have moved about, did I say one word with the judges
        of Israel I commanded to shepherd my people, saying, \u2018Why have you not
        built for me a house of cedar?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So now, thus you shall say to my servant David, \u2018Thus says Yahweh
        of hosts, \u201CI took you from the pasture, from following the sheep, to
        be leader over my people Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and I have been with you wherever you went and have cut down your
        enemies from before you and will make a name for you, like the name of the
        great ones on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I will appoint a place for my people Israel, and I will plant
        them, and they shall dwell in their place and be in anguish no longer. And
        wicked men will no longer wear them down as before, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'from the day that I commanded judges over my people Israel. And I
        will subdue your enemies, and I declare to you that Yahweh will build for
        you a house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And it shall be that when your days are fulfilled to go and sleep
        with your ancestors, then I will raise up your seed after you, who will be
        one of your sons, and I will establish his kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He himself will build for me a house, and I will establish his throne
        forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I myself will be a father to him, and he himself will be a son to
        me. And I will not remove my steadfast love from him as I took it away from
        whoever was before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And I will establish him in my house and in my kingdom forever, and
        his throne will be established forever.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: David\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "David\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 15
      content: 'According to all these words and according to all this revelation,
        thus did Nathan speak to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then King David went and sat before Yahweh and said, \u201CWho am
        I, O Yahweh God, and what is my house that you have brought me thus far? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And this was a small matter in your eyes, O God. And you have spoken
        concerning the house of your servant for a long time and have shown me future
        generations to come, O Yahweh God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'What more can David do to you for honoring your servant? Now you
        know your servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'O Yahweh, for the sake of your servant and according to your heart
        you have done all this greatness, to make known all these great things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'O Yahweh, there is none like you, and there is no God except you,
        according to all that we have heard with our ears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And who is like your people Israel, the one nation upon earth whom
        God went to redeem for himself, to establish for you a reputation for great
        and awesome things, to drive out nations from before your people whom you
        redeemed from Egypt? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And you made your people Israel an everlasting nation for yourself.
        And you, O Yahweh, became their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So now, O Yahweh, let the word that you spoke to your servant and
        to his house be established forever, that you might do what you have spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And let your name be established and be magnified forever, saying,
        \u2018Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel, is Israel\u2019s God, and may the
        house of David your servant be established before you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For you, my God, have informed your servant that you will build a
        house for him. Therefore, your servant has found courage to pray before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So now, O Yahweh, you yourself are God, and you have spoken to your
        servant this good thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And now may you begin to bless the house of your servant to continue
        forever before you, for you, O Yahweh, have blessed. And it will be blessed
        forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Victory over His Enemies"
      title: "David\u2019s Victory over His Enemies"
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened that after David struck the Philistines and subdued
        them, he captured Gath and its villages out of the hand of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he struck Moab, and the Moabites became servants to David, bearing
        tribute. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And David struck Hadadezer, king of Zobah-Hamath, as he set up his
        monument at the Euphrates River. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And David captured from him one thousand chariots, seven thousand
        horsemen, and twenty thousand foot soldiers. And David hamstrung all the
        chariot horses but left one hundred of them to remain for chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when the Arameans of Damascus came to help Hadadezer king of
        Zobah-Hamath, David struck down twenty-two thousand men of Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then David set up garrisons in Aram of Damascus, and the Arameans
        became servants to David, bearing tribute. And Yahweh delivered David wherever
        he went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And David took small round shields of gold that were upon the servants
        of Hadadezer and brought them to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And from Tibhath and from Cun, cities of Hadadezer, David captured
        very much bronze. Solomon made the bronze sea with it along with the columns
        and objects of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when Tou the king of Hamath heard that David had defeated the
        whole army of Hadadezer the king of Zobah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'he sent Hadoram his son to King David to ask him for peace and to
        bless him because he had fought against Hadadezer and defeated him, for Tou
        had been at war with Hadadezer. And he brought with him all the objects of
        gold, silver, and bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'King David dedicated these also to Yahweh, along with the silver
        and gold that he had taken from all the nations, from Edom, Moab, the sons
        of Ammon, the Philistines, and Amalek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Abishai son of Zeruiah defeated eighteen thousand of Edom in
        the Valley of Salt. '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: David\u2019s Administration"
      title: "David\u2019s Administration"
      number: 13
      content: 'And he put garrisons in Edom, and all Edom became servants to David.
        And Yahweh delivered David wherever he went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So David reigned over all Israel, and he administered justice and
        righteousness to all his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Joab son of Zeruiah was over the army, and Jehoshaphat son of
        Ahilud was recorder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Zadok son of Ahitub and Abimelech son of Abiathar were priests,
        and Shavsha was secretary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Benaiah son of Jehoiada was over the Kerethites and the Pelethites.
        And the sons of David were chief officials under the hand of the king. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Ammonites Humiliate David\u2019s Messengers"
      title: "The Ammonites Humiliate David\u2019s Messengers"
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened that after this Nahash the king of the Ammonites
        died, and his son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And David said, \u201CI will deal kindly with Hanun the son of Nahash
        because his father showed kindness to me.\u201D So David sent messengers
        to comfort him concerning his father. And the servants of David came to the
        land of the Ammonites, to Hanun, to comfort him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the princes of the Ammonites said to Hanun, \u201CDo you think
        because David sent comforters to you that David honors your father? Is it
        not for the purpose of exploring so as to overthrow and spy out the land
        that his servants have come to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Hanun took the servants of David and shaved them and cut off their
        garments at the middle, up to the buttocks, and sent them away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And they went and told David concerning the men, and he inquired
        of them, for the men were very disgraced. And the king said, \u201CDwell
        in Jericho until your beards grow out; then return.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when the Ammonites saw that they made themselves odious to David,
        Hanun and the Ammonites sent one thousand talents of silver to hire for themselves
        horses and chariots from Aram-Naharaim, Aram-Maacah, and Zobah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And they hired for themselves thirty-two thousand chariots and the
        king of Maacah and his people, and they came and encamped before Medeba.
        And the Ammonites were gathered from their cities and came to the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And when David heard, he sent Joab and the entire army of mighty
        warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the Ammonites went out and took up positions for battle at the
        entrance of the city. And the kings who had come were alone in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When Joab saw that there was a battle line against him at the front
        and the back, he chose from among the chosen men in Israel and arranged them
        to meet Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the remainder of the people he put in the hand of Abishai his
        brother, and they were arranged to meet the Ammonites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said, \u201CIf Aram is too strong for me, then you must be
        a help to me, but if the Ammonites are too strong for you, then I will help
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Be strong! Let us strengthen ourselves on behalf of our people and
        on behalf of the cities of our God. And may Yahweh do what is good in his
        eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Joab and the people who were with him drew near before Aram for
        battle, and they fled before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And when the Ammonites saw that Aram had fled, they also fled before
        Abishai his brother, and they came to the city. Then Joab came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And when Aram saw that they were defeated before Israel, they sent
        messengers and brought out Aram, who was from beyond the Euphrates, with
        Shophach the commander of the army of Hadadezer before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And when it was told to David, he gathered all Israel and crossed
        the Jordan. And he came to them and was arrayed against them. Then David
        was arrayed to meet Aram in battle, and they fought with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Aram fled before Israel. And David killed from Aram the men of
        seven thousand chariots and forty thousand foot soldiers, and he put to death
        Shophach the commander of the army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And when the servants of Hadadezer saw that they were defeated before
        Israel, they made peace with David and became servants to him. So Aram was
        no longer willing to help the Ammonites.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Capture of Rabbah'
      title: The Capture of Rabbah
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened that in the spring time of year, the time when kings
        go out to battle, Joab led the troops of the army and destroyed the land
        of the Ammonites. And he came and besieged Rabbah, but David remained in
        Jerusalem. And Joab struck Rabbah and destroyed it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And David took the crown of their king from his head and found it
        to weigh a talent of gold. And in it was a precious stone. Then it was placed
        upon the head of David. And he brought out the booty of the city, a large
        amount. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Philistine Giants Slain'
      title: The Philistine Giants Slain
      number: 3
      content: 'And the people who were in it he brought out, and he set them to
        work with saws and iron implements and axes. Thus David did to all the cities
        of the Ammonites. Then David returned, and all the nation went with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And after this there arose a war in Gezer with the Philistines. Then
        Sibbecai the Hushathite struck down Sippai, one of the descendants of the
        Rephaim. And they were subdued. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And again there was war with the Philistines. And Elhanan son of
        Jair struck down Lahmi, the brother of Goliath the Gittite, the shaft of
        whose spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And again there was war in Gath. And there was a very tall man there,
        and he had six fingers on each hand and six toes on each foot, twenty-four
        in all. He himself was also a descendant of the Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he taunted Israel, but Jehonathan son of Shimea, brother of David,
        struck him down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'These were born to the giants in Gath, and they fell by the hand
        of David and by the hand of his servants. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Census of David'
      title: The Census of David
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Satan stood against Israel and urged David to count Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So David said to Joab and to the commanders of the nation, \u201CGo,
        count Israel from Beersheba to Dan and bring a report to me that I might
        know their number.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Joab said, \u201CMay Yahweh add to the people a hundred times
        what they are! Are they not, O my lord the king, all of them the king\u2019s
        servants? Why does my lord seek this? Why would he bring guilt to Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the word of the king prevailed over Joab. Then he went about
        through all Israel and came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Joab gave the number of the enrollment of the people to David.
        And it happened that all Israel was one million one hundred thousand men
        drawing a sword, and in Judah were four hundred and seventy thousand men
        drawing a sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But he did not count Levi and Benjamin among them, for the word of
        the king was repulsive to Joab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But this word was displeasing in the eyes of God, and he struck Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then David said to God, \u201CI have sinned severely in that I have
        done this thing. But now, please forgive the sin of your servant, for I have
        been very foolish.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Yahweh spoke to Gad the seer of David, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CGo, you must speak to David, saying, \u2018Thus says Yahweh:
        \u201CThree choices I offer to you. Choose one of them for yourself that
        I will do to you.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Gad came to David and said to him, \u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018Choose
        for yourself: "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "whether three years of famine or three months of devastation by your
        enemies while the sword of your enemies overtakes you, or three days of the
        sword of Yahweh, with disease in the land and the angel of Yahweh destroying
        throughout all the territory in Israel.\u2019 So now, see what word I should
        return to my sender.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then David said to Gad, \u201CI am very troubled. Let me into the
        hand of Yahweh, for his compassion is very great, but do not let me fall
        into the hand of a man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Yahweh sent a pestilence through Israel, and seventy thousand
        men from Israel fell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And God sent an angel to Jerusalem to destroy it, and as he was about
        to destroy it, Yahweh saw and was grieved on account of the calamity. Then
        he said to the angel, the destroyer, \u201CIt is enough; slacken your hand.\u201D
        And the angel of Yahweh was standing by the threshing floor of Ornan the
        Jebusite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And David lifted his eyes and saw the angel of Yahweh standing between
        earth and heaven, with his sword drawn in his hand, stretched out over Jerusalem.
        Then David and the elders, clothed in sackcloth, fell upon their faces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: David Builds an Altar'
      title: David Builds an Altar
      number: 17
      content: "Then David said to God, \u201CWas it not I who gave a command to
        count the people? Now I am he who has sinned, and I have certainly done wickedness,
        but these sheep, what have they done? O Yahweh, my God, please let your hand
        be against me and against the house of my father, but against your people,
        let there be no plague.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the angel of Yahweh had spoken to Gad to say to David that David
        should go up and erect an altar for Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So David went up at the word of Gad that he had spoken in the name
        of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now Ornan was threshing wheat, and Ornan turned and saw the angel,
        and his four sons with him hid themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then David came to Ornan, and Ornan looked and saw David. And he
        went out from the threshing floor, and they bowed down to David, faces to
        the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then David said to Ornan, \u201CPlease give me the place, the threshing
        floor, that I might build an altar on it to Yahweh; at full price please
        give it to me, that the plague against the people might be stopped.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Ornan said to David, \u201CTake it to yourself; let my lord the
        king do what is good in his eyes. See, I give the cattle for the burnt offerings
        and threshing sledges for the wood and wheat for the grain offering\u2014I
        give it all.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But King David said to Ornan, \u201CNo, for I will certainly buy
        it at full value; indeed, I will not take what is yours for Yahweh and offer
        burnt offerings for nothing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So David gave to Ornan six hundred shekels of gold by weight for
        the place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then David built an altar there to Yahweh, and he offered burnt offerings
        and peace offerings, and he called to Yahweh. And he answered him with fire
        from heaven upon the altar of burnt offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then Yahweh commanded the angel, and he returned his sword to its
        sheath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'At that time, when David saw that Yahweh answered him at the threshing
        floor of Ornan the Jebusite, he sacrificed there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now the tabernacle of Yahweh that Moses had made in the desert and
        the altar of burnt offering were at that time at the high place of Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But David was not able to go before it to seek God, for he was afraid
        on account of the sword of the angel of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Preparations for Building the Temple"
      title: "David\u2019s Preparations for Building the Temple"
      number: 1
      content: " Then David said, \u201CThis will be the house of Yahweh God, and
        this altar of burnt offering for Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And David commanded to assemble the resident aliens who were in the
        land of Israel and appointed stone craftsmen to cut dressed stones to build
        the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And David provided much iron for nails for the doors of the gates
        and for the seams, and abundant copper that could not be weighed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and cedar timbers without number, for the Sidonians and Tyrians brought
        abundant cedars to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Solomon Charged with Building the Temple of Yahweh'
      title: Solomon Charged with Building the Temple of Yahweh
      number: 5
      content: "Then David said, \u201CSolomon my son is a boy and inexperienced,
        and the house built for Yahweh must be exceedingly great in fame and splendor
        throughout every land. I will make preparations for him.\u201D So David provided
        abundant materials before he died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then he called to Solomon his son and commanded him to build a house
        for Yahweh, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And David said to Solomon his son, \u201CI myself had in my heart
        to build a house for the name of Yahweh my God, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "but it happened that the word of Yahweh came over me, saying, \u2018You
        have shed much blood and have made much war; you shall not build a house
        for my name because you have shed much blood upon the ground before me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Behold, a son shall be born to you; he himself will be a man of rest,
        and I will give rest to him from all his enemies all around, for his name
        will be Solomon, and peace and quietness I will give to Israel in his days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He himself will build a house for my name, and he himself will be
        to me a son, and I will be to him as a father, and I will establish the throne
        of his kingdom over Israel forever.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now, my son, Yahweh will be with you, that you may succeed and build
        the house of Yahweh your God as he has spoken concerning you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Only may Yahweh give to you understanding and insight that he might
        give you charge over Israel and the keeping of the law of Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then you will prosper if you take care to do the statutes and judgments
        which Yahweh commanded Moses concerning Israel. Be strong and be courageous;
        fear not and do not be dismayed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now see, with great effort I have made provision for the house of
        Yahweh: 100,000 talents of gold, 1,000,000 talents of silver, and bronze
        and iron that cannot be weighed, for there is an abundance. Also timber and
        stone I have provided, but to these you should add. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And with you there is an abundance of craftsmen: stonecutters, masons,
        carpenters, and everyone skilled in every kind of craftsmanship '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "with gold, silver, bronze, and iron without number. Arise and work!
        Yahweh will be with you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And David commanded all the commanders of Israel to help Solomon
        his son, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIs not Yahweh your God with you? And has he not given you rest
        all around? For he has put in my hand the inhabitants of the land, and the
        land is subdued before Yahweh and before his people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now set your heart and mind to seek Yahweh your Go, and arise and
        build the sanctuary of Yahweh God, that the ark of the covenant of Yahweh
        and the holy vessels of God might be brought into the house built for the
        name of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Organizes the Levites'
      title: David Organizes the Levites
      number: 1
      content: 'Now David was old and full of days. And he made Solomon his son king
        over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he assembled all the commanders of Israel and the priests and
        the Levites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the Levites thirty years old and above were counted, and their
        number according to their head count for the men was thirty-eight thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Of these, David said, \u201CTwenty-four thousand are to direct the
        work of the house of Yahweh, along with six thousand judges and officials, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "four thousand gatekeepers, and four thousand offering praise with
        the instruments that I have made for praise.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And David organized them in divisions according to the sons of Levi:
        to Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the Gershonites were Ladan and Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The sons of Ladan: Jehiel the chief and Zetham and Joel, three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Shimei: Shelomoth, Haziel, and Haran, three. These were
        the heads of the families of Ladan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the sons of Shimei: Jahath, Zina, Jeush, and Beriah; these four
        were the sons of Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Jahath was the chief, and Zizah the second, but Jeush and Beriah
        did not have many sons. They were enrolled as one for the house of a father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel, four. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Amram: Aaron and Moses. And Aaron was set apart to consecrate
        the most holy things. He and his sons were to burn offerings forever before
        Yahweh to serve him and to bless in his name forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But Moses the man of God and his sons were reckoned among the tribe
        of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sons of Moses: Gershom and Eliezer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Gershom: Shebuel the chief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the sons of Eliezer were Rehabiah, the head. And Eliezer had
        no other sons, but the sons of Rehabiah were very many. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The sons of Izhar: Shelomith the chief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Hebron: Jeriah the chief, Amariah the second, Jahaziel
        the third, and Jekameam the fourth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The sons of Uzziel: Micah the chief and Isshiah the second. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. The sons of Mahli: Eleazar and
        Kish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Eleazar died, and he did not have sons, but only daughters. And
        the sons of Kish, their relatives, married them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder, and Jeremoth, three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'These were the sons of Levi according to the house of their fathers,
        the heads of the families, according to their enrollment, by the number of
        the names, according to their head count, who were to do the work of the
        service of the house of Yahweh, from twenty years old and above. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For David said, \u201CYahweh, the God of Israel, has given rest to
        his people, and he dwells in Jerusalem forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And also, the Levites do not need to carry the tabernacle and all
        its vessels for its service.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For by the last words of David, they are the number of the sons of
        Levi, from twenty years old and above. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For their station was to assist the sons of Aaron with the service
        of the house of Yahweh, over the courtyards, over the chambers, and over
        the cleansing of all the sanctified objects, and with the work of the service
        of the house of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'and with the rows of bread, the flour, the grain offering, the wafers
        of unleavened bread, the baked offering, the offering mixed with oil, and
        for all the amounts and measurements. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And they were to stand every morning, thanking and praising Yahweh,
        and likewise in the evening, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and for every burnt offering offered to Yahweh, on Sabbaths, on new
        moon festivals, and at the appointed feasts, according to the customary number
        required of them, regularly before Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And they shall keep the responsibility of the tent of assembly, the
        responsibility of the sanctified objects, and the responsibility of the sons
        of Aaron, their brothers, to serve the house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Organizes the Priests'
      title: David Organizes the Priests
      number: 1
      content: 'And as for the sons of Aaron, these were their divisions. The sons
        of Aaron were Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Nadab and Abihu died before their father, and they had no sons,
        so Eleazar and Ithamar served as priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And David, with Zadok of the sons of Eleazar and Ahimelech of the
        sons of Ithamar, divided them according to their appointments for their service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And more sons of Eleazar were found as heads of the men than the
        sons of Ithamar, so they divided them to the sons of Eleazar to be sixteen
        heads over the house of the fathers, and to the sons of Ithamar over the
        house of the fathers were eight heads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They divided them by lot all alike, for they were commanders of the
        sanctuary and commanders of God from among the sons of Eleazar and the sons
        of Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Shemaiah the son of Nethanel, the scribe, from the Levites, recorded
        them before the king, the princes, Zadok the priest, Ahimelech the son of
        Abiathar, and the heads of the families of the priests and Levites, one father\u2019s
        house drawn by Lot for Eleazar and one drawn by lot for Ithamar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the first lot went out to Jehoiarib, the second to Jedaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'the third to Harim, the fourth to Seorim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'the fifth to Malkijah, the sixth to Mijamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the seventh to Hakkoz, the eighth to Abijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the ninth to Jeshua, the tenth to Shekaniah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the eleventh to Eliashib, the twelfth to Jakim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the thirteenth to Huppah, the fourteenth to Jeshebeab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the fifteenth to Bilgah, the sixteenth to Immer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the seventeenth to Hezir, the eighteenth to Ha-Pizzez, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the nineteenth to Pethahiah, the twentieth to Ezekiel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the twenty-first to Jakin, the twenty-second to Gamul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the twenty-third to Delaiah, the twenty-fourth to Maaziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'These were their appointments for their service to come into the
        house of Yahweh according to their custom by the hand of Aaron their father,
        as Yahweh the God of Israel had commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And as for the remainder of the sons of Levi: of the sons of Amram,
        Shubael; of the sons of Shubael, Jehdeiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Of Rehabiah: of the sons of Rehabiah, Isshiah the chief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Of the Izharites, Shelomoth; of the sons Shelomoth, Jahath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Of the sons of Jeriah, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, Jekameam
        the fourth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Uzziel, Micah; the sons of Micah, Shamur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The brother of Micah, Isshiah; of the sons of Isshiah, Zechariah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi; the sons of Jaaziah, his son.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The sons of Merari: of Jaaziah, his son, Shoham, Zakkur, and Ibri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Of Mahli: Eleazar, who had no sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Of Kish: the sons of Kish, Jerahmeel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder, and Jerimoth. These were the
        sons of the Levites according to the house of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And lots were also cast for these, just as their brothers, the sons
        of Aaron, before David the king, Zadok, Ahimelech, and the heads of the families
        for the priests and for the Levites the fathers, on the principle of the
        chief and younger brother alike.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Organizes the Musicians'
      title: David Organizes the Musicians
      number: 1
      content: 'And David and the commanders of the army set apart for the service
        the sons of Asaph, of Heman, and of Jeduthun, who prophesied with stringed
        instruments, with harps, and with cymbals. And their inventory of the men
        of the work and for their duty was: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'for the sons of Asaph: Zakkur, Joseph, Nethaniah, and Asarelah, sons
        of Asaph, under the hand of Asaph, who prophesied under the hands of the
        king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Of Jeduthun, the sons of Jeduthun: Gedaliah, Zeri, Jeshaiah, Heshabiah,
        and Mattithiah, six, under the hands of their father Jeduthun, who prophesied
        with the stringed instrument with thanksgiving and praise to Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Of Heman, the sons of Heman: Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shebuel
        and Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti and Romamti-ezer, Joshbekashah,
        Mallothi, Hothir, Mahazioth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All these were sons to Heman, the seer of the king, according to
        the words of God to raise a horn. And God had given to Heman fourteen sons
        and three daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'All these were under the direction of their father in the music of
        the house of Yahweh, with cymbals, harps, and stringed instruments for the
        service of the house of God. Asaph, Jeduthun, and Heman were under the direction
        of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And their number, along with their brothers, trained singers, all
        the skilled people for Yahweh, were two hundred and eighty-eight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And they cast lots for responsibilities on the principle of small
        and great alike, teacher with student. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the first lot for Asaph went out to Joseph; the second to Gedaliahu;
        he and his brothers and his twelve sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The third, Zakkur, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the fourth to Izri, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the fifth, Nethaniah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the sixth, Bukkiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the seventh, Jesarelah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the eighth, Jeshaiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the ninth, Mattaniah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the tenth, Shimei, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'eleventh, Azarel, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the twelfth to Hashabiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'to the thirteenth, Shubael, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'to the fourteenth, Mattithiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'to the fifteenth, to Jeremoth, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'to the sixteenth, to Hananiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'to the seventeenth, to Joshbekashah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'to the eighteenth, to Hanani, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'to the nineteenth, to Mallothi, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'to the twentieth, to Eliathah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'to the twenty-first, to Hothir, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'to the twenty-second, to Giddalti, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'to the twenty-third, to Mahazioth, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'to the twenty-fourth, to Romamti-ezer, his sons and his brothers,
        twelve. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Divisions of the Gatekeepers'
      title: The Divisions of the Gatekeepers
      number: 1
      content: 'As for the working groups of the gatekeepers: of the Korahites, Meshelemiah
        the son of Kore, from the sons of Asaph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Meshelemiah had sons: Zechariah the firstborn, Jediael the second,
        Zebadiah the third, Jathniel the fourth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Elam the fifth, Jehohana the sixth, Eliehoenai the seventh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Obed-Edom had sons: Shemaiah the firstborn, Jehozabad the second,
        Joah the third, Sachar the fourth, Nethanel the fifth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seventh, Peullethai the eighth; for
        God blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And to Shemaiah his son were sons born who were rulers in the house
        of their father, for they were mighty warriors of ability. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Shemaiah: Othni, Rephael, Obed, and Elzabad, whose brothers
        were sons of ability, Elihu and Semakiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'All these from the sons of Obed-Edom, they and their sons, and their
        brothers were men of ability with strength for service; sixty-two of Obed-Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Meshelemiah had sons and brothers, sons of ability, eighteen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Hosah, from the sons of Merari, had sons: Shimri the chief (though
        he was not firstborn, his father appointed him as chief), '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Hilkiah the second, Tabaliah the third, Zechariah the fourth: all
        the sons and brothers of Hosah were thirteen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'These working groups of gatekeepers, corresponding to the chief men,
        had responsibilities like their brothers to serve in the house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And they cast lots, small and great alike, by their fathers\u2019
        houses, for their gates.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the lot fell to the east to Shelemiah. As for Zechariah his son,
        a wise counselor, they cast lots. And his lot came out for the north. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'To Obed-Edom went out the south, and to his sons, the storehouses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For Shuppim and Hosah it went out for the west, at the gate of Shalleketh,
        on the road that goes up, guard for guard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'To the east, six Levites; to the north, four daily; to the south,
        four daily; and at the storerooms, two by two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For the court to the west, four at the road, two at the court. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Treasurers and Other Officials'
      title: Treasurers and Other Officials
      number: 19
      content: 'These were the working groups of the gatekeepers among the sons of
        the Korahites and among the sons of Merari. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And of the Levites: Ahijah was over the treasuries of the house of
        God and over the treasuries of the sanctified objects. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Ladan: the sons of the Gershonites belonging to Ladan,
        the heads of the families belonging to Ladan the Gershonite: Jehieli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Jehieli, Zetham and Joel his brother, were over the treasuries
        of the house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Of the Amramites, the Izharites, the Hebronites, and the Ozzielites: '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Shebuel the son of Gershom, the son of Moses, was commander over
        the treasuries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And his brothers: from Eliezer were Rehabiah his son, and Jeshaiah
        his son, and Joram his son, and Zikri his son, and Shelomoth his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'That Shelomoth and his brothers were over all the treasuries of the
        sanctified objects that King David and the heads of the families to the commanders
        of thousands and hundreds and the commanders of the army had dedicated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'From the battles and from the spoil they had dedicated these things
        to strengthen the house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And all that Samuel the seer, and Saul the son of Kish, and Abner
        the son of Ner, and Joab the son of Zeruiah had dedicated\u2014all the dedicated
        gifts were under the hand of Shelomith and his brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For the Izharites: Kenaniah and his sons were appointed to the duties
        outside of Israel as officials and as judges. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'For the Hebronites: Hashabiah and his brothers, one thousand seven
        hundred men of ability, were over the administration of Israel beyond the
        Jordan westward, for all the work of Yahweh and for the service of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For the Hebronites: Jeriah the chief of the Hebronites for the genealogy
        for the families. (In the fortieth year of the reign of David they were examined,
        and there was found among them mighty warriors of strength at Jazer in Gilead.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And his brothers, sons of ability, were two thousand seven hundred
        heads of the families, and King David appointed them over the Reubenites,
        the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, for every matter of God and
        matter of the king. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Military Divisions'
      title: Military Divisions
      number: 1
      content: 'And as for the number of the Israelites, the heads of families, the
        commanders of thousands and hundreds, and their officials who serve the king
        in all matters of the working groups that came and went, month by month,
        throughout all the months of the year, each working group: twenty-four thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Over the first working group for the first month: Jashobeam the son
        of Zabdiel. And he was over his working group of twenty-four thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'From the sons of Perez who was the chief of the commanders of the
        armies for the first month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And over the working groups of the second month: Dodai the Ahohite
        and his working group, and Mikloth the commander. And he was over his working
        group of twenty-four thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The third commander of the army for the third month was Benaiah son
        of Jehoiada the chief priest. And he was over his working group of twenty-four
        thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'This was Benaiah who was a mighty warrior of thirty, and over the
        thirty and his working group was Ammizabad his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The fourth, for the fourth month, was Asahel the brother of Joab
        and his son Zebadiah after him. And he was over his working group of twenty-four
        thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The fifth, for the fifth month, the commander was Shamhuth the Izrahite.
        And he was over his working group of twenty-four thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sixth, for the sixth month, was Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite.
        And he was over his working group of twenty-four thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The seventh, for the seventh month, was Helez the Pelonite, from
        the sons of Ephraim. And he was over his working group of twenty-four thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The eighth, for the eighth month, was Sibbecai the Hushathite of
        the Zerahites. And he was over his working group of twenty-four thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The ninth, for the ninth month, was Abiezer the Anathothite of the
        Benjamites. And he was over his working group of twenty-four thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The tenth, for the tenth month, was Maharai the Netophathite of the
        Zerahites. And he was over his working group of twenty-four thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The eleventh, for the eleventh month, was Benaiah the Pirathonite
        from the sons of Ephraim. And he was over his working group of twenty-four
        thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Leaders of the Tribes and Other High Ranking Officials'
      title: Leaders of the Tribes and Other High Ranking Officials
      number: 15
      content: 'The twelfth, for the twelfth month, was Heldai the Netophathite,
        of Othniel. And he was over his working group of twenty-four thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And over the tribes of Israel, for the Reubenites: the commander
        was Eliezer the son of Zikri. For the Simeonites: Shephatiah the son of Maacah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For Levi: Hashabiah the son of Kemuel. For Aaron, Zadok. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For Judah: Elihu, from the brothers of David. For Issachar: Omri
        the son of Michael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For Zebulun: Ishmaiah the son of Obadiah. For Naphtali: Jerimoth
        the son of Azriel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For the Ephraimites: Hoshea the son of Azaziah. For the half-tribe
        of Manasseh: Joel the son of Pedaiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For the half-tribe of Manasseh in Gilead: Iddo the son of Zechariah.
        For Benjamin: Jaasiel son of Abner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For Dan: Azarel the son of Jeroham. These were the commanders of
        the tribes of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And David did not take a census of those twenty years old or under
        because Yahweh promised to make Israel more numerous than the stars of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Joab the son of Zeruiah began to count, but he did not finish. But
        wrath came upon Israel concerning this, and the number was not included in
        the chronicles of King David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And over the treasury rooms of the king was Azmaveth the son of Adiel.
        And over the treasuries in the country, in the cities, in the unwalled villages,
        and in the towers was Jonathan the son of Uzziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And over those who did the work in the field to till the soil was
        Ezri the son of Kelub. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And over the vineyards was Shemei the Ramathite. And over the produce
        in the vineyards for the storehouses of the wine was Zabdi the Shiphmite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And over the olive trees and the sycamore trees that were in the
        Shephelah was Baal-Hanan the Gederite. And over the treasury houses of olive
        oil was Joash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And over the cattle pastured in the Sharon was Shitrai the Sharonite.
        And over the cattle in the valley was Shaphat the son of Adlai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And over the camels was Obil the Ishmaelite. And over the female
        donkeys was Jehdeiah the Meronothite. And over the sheep was Jaziz the Hagrite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'All of these were officials of the property of King David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And Jehonathan the uncle of David was an adviser, a man of insight,
        and he was a scribe. And Jehiel the son of Hachmoni was with the sons of
        the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And Ahithophel was an adviser to the king, and Hushai the Arkite
        was a friend of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And after Ahithophel came Jehoiada, the son of Benaiah, and Abiathar.
        And Joab was the commander of the king\u2019s army. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Charge to Israel"
      title: "David\u2019s Charge to Israel"
      number: 1
      content: 'Then David assembled all the commanders of Israel, the commanders
        of the tribes and the commanders of working groups who served the king, and
        the commanders of thousands, the commanders of hundreds, and the commanders
        over all the property of the king and his sons, with the court officials
        and mighty warriors, and all the mighty warriors of ability, at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And King David rose to his feet and said, \u201CListen to me, my
        brothers and my people. I myself wanted to build a house of rest for the
        ark of the covenant of Yahweh and the footstool of our God, and I prepared
        to build. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But God said to me, \u2018You may not build a house for my name because
        you are a man of war, and you have shed blood.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Yahweh the God of Israel chose me from all of the house of my
        father to be king over Israel forever, for he chose Judah as leader, and
        in the house of Judah, the house of my father, and among the sons of my father
        he took pleasure in me to reign over all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And from all my sons\u2014for Yahweh has given many sons to me\u2014he
        has chosen Solomon my son to sit on the throne of the kingdom of Yahweh over
        Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he said to me, \u2018Solomon your son, he himself shall build
        my house and my courts, for I have chosen him as a son to myself, and I myself
        will be as a father to him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and I will establish his kingdom forever if he firmly performs my
        commandments and my judgments as he has to this day.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: "8: David\u2019s Charge to Solomon"
      title: "David\u2019s Charge to Solomon"
      number: 8
      content: "So now in the sight of all Israel, the assembly of Yahweh, and in
        the hearing of our God, observe and seek all the commandments of Yahweh your
        God so that you may take possession of this good land and bestow it as an
        inheritance to your children after you forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd you, Solomon my son, know the God of your father and serve
        him with a whole heart and a willing mind, for Yahweh searches all hearts
        and understands every plan and all thoughts. If you seek him, he will be
        found by you, but if you abandon him, he will reject you forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Look now, for Yahweh has chosen you to build a house for the sanctuary;
        be strong and do it!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then David gave to Solomon his son the plan of the vestibule and
        of its houses, its treasuries, its upper rooms, its inner chambers, and of
        the house of the lid of the ark, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and the plan of all that he had in mind for the courtyards of the
        house of Yahweh and for all the surrounding storage rooms, the treasuries
        of the house of God, and the treasuries for sanctified objects, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and for the working groups of the priests and the Levites, and for
        all the work of the service of the house of Yahweh, and for all the vessels
        for the service of the house of Yahweh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and for the gold, according to the weight of the gold for all the
        vessels of the service, and the service of all the vessels of silver according
        to the weight of all the vessels for every kind of service.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the weight of the golden lampstands and the golden lamps, the
        weight of each lampstand and each lamp, and the silver according to the weight
        of a lampstand and its lamp, according to the use of each lampstand,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and the weight of gold for the tables of the arranged bread, each
        table, and silver for the tables of silver, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and pure gold for the three-pronged meat forks, and the bowls and
        the pitchers, and for the golden bowls, by weight for each bowl, and for
        the silver bowls, by weight for each bowl,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and for the altar of incense made of refined gold, by weight, and
        gold for the plan for the chariot\u2014the cherubim with outspread and covering
        wings over the ark of the covenant of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CAll this I give you in writing; from the hand of Yahweh he
        instructed me about all the workings of this plan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then David said to Solomon his son, \u201CBe strong and courageous,
        and do this! Do not be afraid and do not be dismayed, for Yahweh God, my
        God, is with you. He will not fail you and will not forsake you until all
        the work of the service of the house of Yahweh is finished. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And behold, the working groups of the priests and the Levites for
        all the service of the house of God; and with you in all the work for all
        those willing with the skill for every service, and the commanders and all
        the people for all your commands.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Offerings for the Temple'
      title: Offerings for the Temple
      number: 1
      content: "Then David the king said to all the assembly, \u201CGod has chosen
        Solomon my son alone, a young man and inexperienced, and the work is great,
        for the citadel is not for humankind, but for Yahweh God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I have provided for the house of my God according to all my strength,
        the gold for the things of gold, the silver for the things of silver, the
        bronze for the things of bronze, the iron for the things of iron, and the
        wood for the things of wood, along with an abundance of onyx stones, stones
        for settings, stones of turquoise, and variegated stones, and all kinds of
        precious stones and alabaster stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And moreover, with respect to my provisions for the house of my God
        I have a treasure of gold and silver that I have given to the house of my
        God above all that I have provided for the holy house: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'three thousand talents of gold from the gold of Ophir and seven thousand
        talents of refined silver to overlay the walls of the houses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "gold for the golden things and silver for the silver things, for
        all the work by the hand of skilled craftsmen. Now who will offer willingly,
        consecrating himself today to Yahweh?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the commanders of the families, the commanders of the tribes
        of Israel, and the commanders of thousands and hundreds, and the commanders
        of the work of the king offered themselves willingly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And they gave for the service of the house of God five thousand talents
        and ten thousand darics of gold, ten thousand talents of silver, eighteen
        thousand talents of bronze, and one hundred thousand talents of iron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And whoever had precious stones gave them to the treasury of the
        house of Yahweh under the authority of Jehiel the Gershonite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the people rejoiced over their freewill offering, for with a
        whole heart they had willingly offered to Yahweh, and King David also rejoiced
        with great joy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then David blessed Yahweh in the sight of all the assembly, and David
        said, \u201CBlessed are you, O Yahweh, God of Israel, our father forever
        and ever! "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'To you, O Yahweh, is the greatness and the power and the splendor
        and the glory and the strength, for everything in the heavens and in the
        earth. Yours, O Yahweh, is the kingdom and exaltation over all as head! '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And wealth and glory are from you, and you rule over all. And in
        your hand is power and might. And in your hand is power to make great and
        to give strength to all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And now, our God, we give thanks to you and offer praise to the name
        of your splendor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And indeed, who am I, and who are my people that we retain power
        to offer according to these offerings willingly? For everything is from you,
        and from your hand we have given to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For we are strangers before you and sojourners like all our ancestors.
        Our days are like the shadow upon earth, and there is no hope of abiding. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'O Yahweh our God, all this abundance that we have provided to build
        for you a house for your holy name is from your hand, and all of it is yours. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And I know, my God, that you yourself test the heart and are pleased
        with uprightness. I, in the uprightness of my heart, have willingly offered
        all these things, and now I have seen your people who are found here willingly
        offer to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'O Yahweh, God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, our ancestors, keep
        this forever as a plan and thoughts of the heart of your people, and establish
        their heart toward you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Grant to Solomon my son a heart of peace to keep your commands, your
        statutes, and your regulations to do everything, and to build the citadel
        for which I have provided.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "20: Solomon\u2019s Coronation"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Coronation"
      number: 20
      content: "And David said to all the assembly, \u201CBless Yahweh your God!\u201D
        And all the assembly blessed Yahweh, the God of their ancestors. And they
        bowed down and prostrated themselves before Yahweh and the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And they offered sacrifices to Yahweh, and on that next day they
        offered burnt offerings to Yahweh: one thousand bulls, one thousand rams,
        one thousand lambs, with their libations and sacrifices in abundance for
        all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And they ate and drank before Yahweh on that day with great joy.
        And they made Solomon the son of David king the second time, and they anointed
        him commander for Yahweh, and Zadok the priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then Solomon sat upon the throne of Yahweh as king in place of David
        his father. And he prospered, and all Israel obeyed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And all the officials and mighty warriors, and also all the sons
        of King David, pledged allegiance to King Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: The Death of King David'
      title: The Death of King David
      number: 25
      content: 'And Yahweh made Solomon exceedingly great in the sight of all Israel,
        and he bestowed upon him royal splendor that was not bestowed upon any king
        before him in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And David the son of Jesse reigned over all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the days that he reigned over Israel were forty years. In Hebron
        he reigned seven years, and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty-three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he died in a good old age, full of days, wealth, and honor. And
        Solomon his son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now the words of King David, from the first to the last, see, they
        are written among the words of Samuel the seer, and among the words of Nathan
        the prophet, and among the words of Gad the seer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
